sociate professor of medicine at the University of Illinois at Chicago College of Medicine  representative sample of prospectively enrolled patients with various stages of chronic kidney disease related disparity observed in patients with CKD Ricardo hopes the study increases public and care provider awareness of the higher risk of kidney failure and death among men U  DK        U  DK        U  DK        U  DK        U  DK        U  DK        U  DK       and U  DK        Additional funding to individual researchers was noted in the study Co authors on the study from UIC are Anjella Manoharan  Dr  Martha Daviglus and Dr  James Lash Additional co authors are Wei Yang and Daohang Sha of the University of Pennsylvania  Dr  Lawrence Appel of Johns Hopkins University  Dr  Jing Chen and Dr  Marie Krousel Wood of Tulane University  Dr  Susan Steigerwalt of the University of Michigan  Dr  Jackson Wright and Dr  Mahboob Rahman of Case Western University  Dr  Sylvia Rosas of Harvard Medical School  Dr  Milda Saunders of the University of Chicago  Dr  Kumar Sharma of the University of California and CRIC Study investigators  n nContact n nJacqueline Carey n t t t t t t t             njmcarey uic edu ntwitter com JCareyUIC n n n Contact  nJacqueline Carey n t t t t t t t             njmcarey uic edu ntwitter com JCareyUIC n Jacqueline Carey jmcarey uic edu twitter com JCareyUIC Categories  nHealth Sciences Colleges  Research  Health Sciences Colleges Research Topics chronic kidney disease  College of Medicine  health disparities chronic kidney disease College of Medicine health disparities  n nUIC Logo n n n n UIC Logo  n         t  Today n       t t   Contact uictoday uic edu Social Media Accounts For the Media Experts Guide Advertise in UIC News Submit Announcements Submit an Event Subscribe to UIC Today UIC edu links UIC edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus Directory Disability Resources Emergency Information Event Calendar Job Openings Library Maps UI Health Veterans Affai